73Object::~Object()
74{
75 if (!isItem())
76 {
77 if (!m_inQueue && !IsInWorld())
78 {
79 m_instanceId = INSTANCEID_NOT_IN_WORLD;
80
81 for (uint8_t i = 0; i < CURRENT_SPELL_MAX; ++i)
82 {
83 if (m_currentSpell[i] != nullptr)
84 interruptSpellWithSpellType(static_cast<CurrentSpellType>(i));
85 }
86
87 for (auto travelingSpellItr = m_travelingSpells.begin(); travelingSpellItr != m_travelingSpells.end();)
88 {
89 delete (*travelingSpellItr).first;
90 travelingSpellItr = m_travelingSpells.erase(travelingSpellItr);
91 }
92
93 removeGarbageSpells();
94
95 for (auto pendingSpellItr = m_pendingSpells.begin(); pendingSpellItr != m_pendingSpells.end();)
96 {
97 delete (*pendingSpellItr);
98 pendingSpellItr = m_pendingSpells.erase(pendingSpellItr);
99 }
100
101 sEventMgr.RemoveEvents(this);
102 }
103 }
104}

106bool Object::write(const uint8_t& member, uint8_t val, bool skipObjectUpdate/* = false*/)
107{
108 if (member == val)
109 return false;
110
111 const auto member_ptr = const_cast<uint8_t*>(&member);
112 *member_ptr = val;
113
114 auto distance = static_cast<uint32_t>(member_ptr - wow_data_ptr);
115 distance -= distance % 4;
116 distance /= 4;
117
118 m_updateMask.SetBit(distance);
119
120 if (!skipObjectUpdate)
121 updateObject();
122
123 return true;
124}
125
126bool Object::write(const uint16_t& member, uint16_t val, bool skipObjectUpdate/* = false*/)
127{
128 if (member == val)
129 return false;
130
131 const auto nonconst_member = const_cast<uint16_t*>(&member);
132 *nonconst_member = val;
133
134 const auto member_ptr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(nonconst_member);
135 auto distance = static_cast<uint32_t>(member_ptr - wow_data_ptr);
136 distance /= 4;
137
138 m_updateMask.SetBit(distance);
139 m_updateMask.SetBit(distance + 1);
140
141 if (!skipObjectUpdate)
142 updateObject();
143
144 return true;
145}

268bool Object::write(const uint64_t& member, uint32_t low, uint32_t high, bool skipObjectUpdate/* = false*/)
269{
270 const auto nonconst_member = const_cast<uint64_t*>(&member);
271 const auto low_ptr = reinterpret_cast<uint32_t*>(*nonconst_member);
272 const auto high_ptr = low_ptr + 1;
273
274 if (*low_ptr == low && *high_ptr == high)
275 return false;
276
277 *low_ptr = low;
278 *high_ptr = high;
279
280 const auto member_ptr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(nonconst_member);
281 auto distance = static_cast<uint32_t>(member_ptr - wow_data_ptr);
282 distance /= 4;
283
284 m_updateMask.SetBit(distance);
285 m_updateMask.SetBit(distance + 1);
286
287 if (!skipObjectUpdate)
288 updateObject();
289
290 return true;
291}

421uint32_t Object::buildCreateUpdateBlockForPlayer(ByteBuffer* data, Player* target)
422{
423 if (m_wowGuid.GetNewGuidLen() <= 0)
424 return 0;
425
426 if (target == nullptr)
427 return 0;
428
429 uint8_t updateType = UPDATETYPE_CREATE_OBJECT;
430#if VERSION_STRING <= TBC
431 uint8_t updateFlags = static_cast<uint8_t>(m_updateFlag);
432#endif
433
434#if VERSION_STRING >= WotLK
435 uint16_t updateFlags = m_updateFlag;
436#endif
437
438 if (target == this)
439 updateFlags |= UPDATEFLAG_SELF;
440
441 switch (m_objectTypeId)
442 {
443 case TYPEID_PLAYER:
444 case TYPEID_DYNAMICOBJECT:
445 case TYPEID_CORPSE:
446 case TYPEID_AREATRIGGER:
447 {
448 updateType = UPDATETYPE_CREATE_OBJECT2;
449 } break;
450 case TYPEID_UNIT:
451 {
452 ///\ todo: vehicles?
453 if (isPet())
454 {
455 updateType = UPDATETYPE_CREATE_OBJECT2;
456 }
457 else if (isSummon())
458 {
459 // Only player summons
460 const auto summoner = getWorldMapPlayer(static_cast<Summon*>(this)->getSummonedByGuid());
461 if (summoner != nullptr)
462 updateType = UPDATETYPE_CREATE_OBJECT2;
463 }
464 } break;
465 case TYPEID_GAMEOBJECT:
466 {
467 // Only player gameobjects
468 if (static_cast<GameObject*>(this)->getPlayerOwner() != nullptr)
469 updateType = UPDATETYPE_CREATE_OBJECT2;
470 } break;
471 default:
472 break;
473 }
474
475 if (!(updateFlags & UPDATEFLAG_LIVING))
476 {
477 if (obj_movement_info.transport_guid != 0)
478 updateFlags |= UPDATEFLAG_HAS_POSITION;
479 }
480
481 if (updateFlags & UPDATEFLAG_HAS_POSITION)
482 {
483 if (isGameObject())
484 {
485 const auto gameObj = static_cast<GameObject*>(this);
486 switch (gameObj->getGoType())
487 {
488 case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_TRAP:
489 case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_DUEL_ARBITER:
490 case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_FLAGSTAND:
491 case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_FLAGDROP:
492 updateType = UPDATETYPE_CREATE_OBJECT2;
493 break;
494 case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_TRANSPORT:
495 case GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_MO_TRANSPORT:
496 updateFlags |= UPDATEFLAG_TRANSPORT;
497 break;
498 default:
499 // Set update type for other gameobjects only if it's created by a player
500 if (gameObj->getPlayerOwner() != nullptr)
501 updateType = UPDATETYPE_CREATE_OBJECT2;
502 break;
503 }
504 }
505 }
506
507#ifdef FT_VEHICLES
508 if (isVehicle())
509 updateFlags |= UPDATEFLAG_VEHICLE;
510#endif
511
512 if (isCreatureOrPlayer())
513 {
514 if (dynamic_cast<Unit*>(this)->getTargetGuid() != 0)
515 updateFlags |= UPDATEFLAG_HAS_TARGET;
516 }
517
518 // build our actual update
519 *data << uint8_t(updateType);
520 *data << m_wowGuid;
521 *data << uint8_t(m_objectTypeId);
522
523 buildMovementUpdate(data, updateFlags, target);
524
525 // we have dirty data, or are creating for ourself.
526 UpdateMask updateMask;
527 updateMask.SetCount(m_valuesCount);
528 setCreateBits(&updateMask, target);
529
530 // this will cache automatically if needed
531 buildValuesUpdate(updateType, data, &updateMask, target);
532#if VERSION_STRING == Mop
533 *data << uint8_t(0);
534#endif
535 // Update count
536 return 1;
537}

539void Object::forceBuildUpdateValueForField(uint32_t field, Player* target)
540{
541 if (target == nullptr)
542 return;
543
544 m_updateMask.SetBit(field);
545
546 ByteBuffer buffer(500);
547 BuildValuesUpdateBlockForPlayer(&buffer, target);
548 target->getUpdateMgr().pushUpdateData(&buffer, 1);
549}
550
551void Object::forceBuildUpdateValueForFields(uint32_t const* fields, Player* target)
552{
553 if (target == nullptr)
554 return;
555
556 for (uint32_t i = 0; fields[i] != 0; ++i)
557 m_updateMask.SetBit(fields[i]);
558
559 ByteBuffer buffer(500);
560 BuildValuesUpdateBlockForPlayer(&buffer, target);
561 target->getUpdateMgr().pushUpdateData(&buffer, 1);
562}

605Spell* Object::getCurrentSpellById(uint32_t spellId) const
606{
607 for (uint8_t i = 0; i < CURRENT_SPELL_MAX; ++i)
608 {
609 if (m_currentSpell[i] == nullptr)
610 continue;
611 if (m_currentSpell[i]->getSpellInfo()->getId() == spellId)
612 return m_currentSpell[i];
613 }
614 return nullptr;

617void Object::setCurrentSpell(Spell* curSpell)
618{
619 if (curSpell != nullptr) // curSpell cannot be nullptr
620 {
621 // Get current spell type
622 CurrentSpellType spellType = CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL;
623 if (curSpell->getSpellInfo()->isOnNextMeleeAttack())
624 {
625 // Melee spell
626 spellType = CURRENT_MELEE_SPELL;
627 }
628 else if (curSpell->getSpellInfo()->isRangedAutoRepeat())
629 {
630 // Autorepeat spells (Auto shot / Shoot (wand))
631 spellType = CURRENT_AUTOREPEAT_SPELL;
632 }
633 else if (curSpell->getSpellInfo()->isChanneled())
634 {
635 // Channeled spells
636 spellType = CURRENT_CHANNELED_SPELL;
637 }
638
639 // We've already set this spell to current spell, ignore
640 if (curSpell == m_currentSpell[spellType])
641 return;
642
643 // Interrupt spell with same spell type
644 interruptSpellWithSpellType(spellType);
645
646 // Handle spelltype specific cases
647 switch (spellType)
648 {
649 case CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL:
650 {
651 // Generic spells break channeled spells
652 interruptSpellWithSpellType(CURRENT_CHANNELED_SPELL);
653
654 if (m_currentSpell[CURRENT_AUTOREPEAT_SPELL] != nullptr)
655 {
656 // Generic spells do not break Auto Shot
657 if (m_currentSpell[CURRENT_AUTOREPEAT_SPELL]->getSpellInfo()->getId() != 75)
658 interruptSpellWithSpellType(CURRENT_AUTOREPEAT_SPELL);
659 }
660 } break;
661 case CURRENT_CHANNELED_SPELL:
662 {
663 // Channeled spells break generic spells
664 interruptSpellWithSpellType(CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL);
665 // as well break channeled spells too
666 interruptSpellWithSpellType(CURRENT_CHANNELED_SPELL);
667
668 // Also break autorepeat spells, unless it's Auto Shot
669 if (m_currentSpell[CURRENT_AUTOREPEAT_SPELL] != nullptr && m_currentSpell[CURRENT_AUTOREPEAT_SPELL]->getSpellInfo()->getId() != 75)
670 interruptSpellWithSpellType(CURRENT_AUTOREPEAT_SPELL);
671 } break;
672 case CURRENT_AUTOREPEAT_SPELL:
673 {
674 // Other autorepeats than Auto Shot break non-delayed generic and channeled spells
675 if (curSpell->getSpellInfo()->getId() != 75)
676 {
677 interruptSpellWithSpellType(CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL);
678 interruptSpellWithSpellType(CURRENT_CHANNELED_SPELL);
679 }
680
681 if (isPlayer())
682 static_cast<Player*>(this)->m_FirstCastAutoRepeat = true;
683 } break;
684 default:
685 break;
686 }
687
688 // If spell is not yet cancelled, force it
689 if (m_currentSpell[spellType] != nullptr)
690 m_currentSpell[spellType]->finish(false);
691
692 // Set new current spell
693 m_currentSpell[spellType] = curSpell;
694 }
695 else
696 {
697 sLogger.failure("Object::setCurrentSpell tried to set invalid current spell (nullptr)");
698 }
699}
700
701void Object::interruptSpell(uint32_t spellId, bool checkMeleeSpell)
702{
703 for (uint8_t i = 0; i < CURRENT_SPELL_MAX; ++i)
704 {
705 if (!checkMeleeSpell && i == CURRENT_MELEE_SPELL)
706 continue;
707
708 if (m_currentSpell[i] != nullptr && (spellId == 0 || m_currentSpell[i]->getSpellInfo()->getId() == spellId))
709 interruptSpellWithSpellType(CurrentSpellType(i));
710 }
711}
712
713void Object::interruptSpellWithSpellType(CurrentSpellType spellType)
714{
715 Spell* curSpell = m_currentSpell[spellType];
716 if (curSpell != nullptr)
717 {
718 if (spellType == CURRENT_AUTOREPEAT_SPELL)
719 {
720 if (isPlayer() && IsInWorld())
721 {
722 // Send server-side cancel message
723 WorldPacket data(SMSG_CANCEL_AUTO_REPEAT, 8);
724 data << GetNewGUID();
725 sendMessageToSet(&data, false);
726 }
727 }
728
729 // Cancel spell
730 curSpell->cancel();
731 m_currentSpell[spellType] = nullptr;
732 }
733}
734
735bool Object::isCastingSpell(bool skipChanneled /*= false*/, bool skipAutorepeat /*= false*/, bool isAutoshoot /*= false*/) const
736{
737 // Check generic spell, but ignore finished spells
738 if (m_currentSpell[CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL] != nullptr && m_currentSpell[CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL]->getState() != SPELL_STATE_FINISHED && m_currentSpell[CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL]->getCastTimeLeft() > 0 &&
739 (!isAutoshoot || !(m_currentSpell[CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL]->getSpellInfo()->getAttributesExB() & ATTRIBUTESEXB_NOT_RESET_AUTO_ATTACKS)))
740 {
741 return true;
742 }
743
744 // If not skipped, check channeled spell
745 if (!skipChanneled && m_currentSpell[CURRENT_CHANNELED_SPELL] != nullptr && m_currentSpell[CURRENT_CHANNELED_SPELL]->getState() != SPELL_STATE_FINISHED &&
746 (!isAutoshoot || !(m_currentSpell[CURRENT_CHANNELED_SPELL]->getSpellInfo()->getAttributesExB() & ATTRIBUTESEXB_NOT_RESET_AUTO_ATTACKS)))
747 {
748 return true;
749 }
750
751 // If not skipped, check autorepeat spell
752 if (!skipAutorepeat && m_currentSpell[CURRENT_AUTOREPEAT_SPELL] != nullptr)
753 {
754 return true;
755 }
756 return false;
757}
758
759Spell* Object::findCurrentCastedSpellBySpellId(uint32_t spellId)
760{
761 for (uint8_t i = 0; i < CURRENT_SPELL_MAX; ++i)
762 {
763 if (m_currentSpell[i] == nullptr)
764 continue;
765 if (m_currentSpell[i]->getSpellInfo()->getId() == spellId)
766 return m_currentSpell[i];
767 }
768 return nullptr;
769}
770
771DamageInfo Object::doSpellDamage(Unit* victim, uint32_t spellId, float_t dmg, uint8_t effIndex, bool isTriggered/* = false*/, bool isPeriodic/* = false*/, bool isLeech/* = false*/, bool forceCrit/* = false*/, Spell* spell/* = nullptr*/, Aura* aur/* = nullptr*/, AuraEffectModifier* aurEff/* = nullptr*/)
772{
773 if (victim == nullptr || !victim->isAlive())
774 return DamageInfo();
775
776 const auto spellInfo = sSpellMgr.getSpellInfo(spellId);
777 if (spellInfo == nullptr)
778 return DamageInfo();
779
780 float_t damage = dmg;
781 const auto school = spellInfo->getFirstSchoolFromSchoolMask();
782
783 // Create damage info
784 DamageInfo dmgInfo;
785 dmgInfo.schoolMask = SchoolMask(spellInfo->getSchoolMask());
786 dmgInfo.isCritical = forceCrit;
787 dmgInfo.isPeriodic = isPeriodic;
788
789 // Check if victim is immune to this school
790 // or if victim has god mode cheat
791 if (victim->m_schoolImmunityList[school] != 0 ||
792 (victim->isPlayer() && static_cast<Player*>(victim)->m_cheats.hasGodModeCheat))
793 {
794 if (isCreatureOrPlayer())
795 static_cast<Unit*>(this)->sendSpellOrDamageImmune(getGuid(), victim, spellId);
796
797 return DamageInfo();
798 }
799
800 // Setup proc flags
801 dmgInfo.victimProcFlags = PROC_ON_TAKEN_ANY_DAMAGE;
802
803 if (!isPeriodic)
804 {
805 switch (spellInfo->getDmgClass())
806 {
807 case SPELL_DMG_TYPE_NONE:
808 dmgInfo.attackerProcFlags |= PROC_ON_DONE_NEGATIVE_SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_NONE;
809 dmgInfo.victimProcFlags |= PROC_ON_TAKEN_NEGATIVE_SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_NONE;
810 break;
811 case SPELL_DMG_TYPE_MAGIC:
812 dmgInfo.attackerProcFlags |= PROC_ON_DONE_NEGATIVE_SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MAGIC;
813 dmgInfo.victimProcFlags |= PROC_ON_TAKEN_NEGATIVE_SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MAGIC;
814 break;
815 case SPELL_DMG_TYPE_MELEE:
816 dmgInfo.attackerProcFlags |= PROC_ON_DONE_MELEE_SPELL_HIT;
817 dmgInfo.victimProcFlags |= PROC_ON_TAKEN_MELEE_SPELL_HIT;
818 break;
819 case SPELL_DMG_TYPE_RANGED:
820 dmgInfo.attackerProcFlags |= PROC_ON_DONE_RANGED_SPELL_HIT;
821 dmgInfo.victimProcFlags |= PROC_ON_TAKEN_RANGED_SPELL_HIT;
822 break;
823 default:
824 break;
825 }
826 }
827 else
828 {
829 dmgInfo.attackerProcFlags |= PROC_ON_DONE_PERIODIC;
830 dmgInfo.victimProcFlags |= PROC_ON_TAKEN_PERIODIC;
831 }
832
833 if (isCreatureOrPlayer())
834 {
835 const auto casterUnit = static_cast<Unit*>(this);
836 casterUnit->removeAllAurasByAuraInterruptFlag(AURA_INTERRUPT_ON_START_ATTACK);
837 }
838
839 // Mage talent - Torment the Weak
840 if (isPlayer() && (victim->hasAuraWithMechanic(MECHANIC_ENSNARED) || victim->hasAuraWithMechanic(MECHANIC_DAZED)))
841 {
842 const auto pct = static_cast<float_t>(static_cast<Player*>(this)->m_increaseDmgSnaredSlowed);
843 damage = damage * (1.0f + (pct / 100.0f));
844 }
845
846 // Add creature type bonuses
847 if (isPlayer() && victim->isCreature())
848 {
849 const auto plr = static_cast<Player*>(this);
850 const auto cre = static_cast<Creature*>(victim);
851 const auto type = cre->GetCreatureProperties()->Type;
852
853 damage += damage * plr->m_increaseDamageByTypePct[type];
854 if (isPeriodic)
855 {
856 if (aur != nullptr && aurEff != nullptr)
857 damage += static_cast<float_t>(plr->m_increaseDamageByType[type] / aur->getPeriodicTickCountForEffect(aurEff->getEffectIndex()));
858 }
859 else
860 {
861 damage += static_cast<float_t>(plr->m_increaseDamageByType[type]);
862 }
863 }
864
865 // Check if spell can crit
866 if (damage > 0.0f && isCreatureOrPlayer())
867 {
868 // If the damage is forced to be crit, do not alter it
869 if (!dmgInfo.isCritical && !(spellInfo->getAttributesExB() & ATTRIBUTESEXB_CANT_CRIT))
870 {
871 if (isPeriodic)
872 {
873 // For periodic effects use aura's own crit chance
874 if (aur != nullptr)
875 dmgInfo.isCritical = Util::checkChance(aur->getCritChance());
876 }
877 else if (spell != nullptr)
878 {
879 dmgInfo.isCritical = static_cast<Unit*>(this)->isCriticalDamageForSpell(victim, spell);
880 }
881 }
882
883 // Get critical spell damage bonus
884 if (dmgInfo.isCritical)
885 damage = static_cast<Unit*>(this)->getCriticalDamageBonusForSpell(damage, victim, spell, aur);
886 }
887
888 // Calculate damage reduction
889 damage += damage * victim->m_damageTakenPctMod[school];
890 damage += damage * victim->m_modDamageTakenByMechPct[spellInfo->getMechanicsType()];
891 if (isPeriodic)
892 {
893 if (aur != nullptr && aurEff != nullptr)
894 damage += static_cast<float_t>(victim->m_damageTakenMod[school] / aur->getPeriodicTickCountForEffect(aurEff->getEffectIndex()));
895 }
896 else
897 {
898 damage += static_cast<float_t>(victim->m_damageTakenMod[school]);
899 }
900
901 // Resilience
902 ///\ todo: move this elsewhere and fix this
903 float_t damageReductionPct = 1.0f;
904 if (victim->isPlayer())
905 {
906 auto resilienceValue = static_cast<Player*>(victim)->calcRating(CR_CRIT_TAKEN_SPELL) / 100.0f;
907 if (resilienceValue > 1.0f)
908 resilienceValue = 1.0f;
909 damageReductionPct -= resilienceValue;
910 }
911 damage *= damageReductionPct;
912
913 if (damage < 0.0f)
914 damage = 0.0f;
915
916 // For periodic auras convert the float amount to integer and save the damage fraction for next tick
917 if (isPeriodic && aur != nullptr && aurEff != nullptr)
918 {
919 damage += aurEff->getEffectDamageFraction();
920 if (aur->getTimeLeft() >= aurEff->getEffectAmplitude())
921 {
922 dmgInfo.fullDamage = static_cast<int32_t>(damage);
923 aurEff->setEffectDamageFraction(damage - dmgInfo.fullDamage);
924 }
925 else
926 {
927 // In case this is the last tick, just round the value
928 dmgInfo.fullDamage = static_cast<int32_t>(std::round(damage));
929 }
930 }
931 else
932 {
933 // If this is a direct damage spell just round the value
934 dmgInfo.fullDamage = static_cast<int32_t>(std::round(damage));
935 }
936
937 dmgInfo.realDamage = dmgInfo.fullDamage;
938
939 // Calculate resistance reduction
940 if (dmgInfo.realDamage > 0 && isCreatureOrPlayer() && !(isPeriodic && school == SCHOOL_NORMAL))
941 {
942 static_cast<Unit*>(this)->calculateResistanceReduction(victim, &dmgInfo, spellInfo, 0.0f);
943 if (dmgInfo.resistedDamage > static_cast<uint32_t>(dmgInfo.fullDamage))
944 dmgInfo.realDamage = 0;
945 else
946 dmgInfo.realDamage = dmgInfo.fullDamage - dmgInfo.resistedDamage;
947 }
948
949 // Check for absorb effects
950 dmgInfo.absorbedDamage = victim->absorbDamage(SchoolMask(spellInfo->getSchoolMask()), &dmgInfo.realDamage);
951 const auto manaShieldAbsorb = victim->getManaShieldAbsorbedDamage(dmgInfo.realDamage);
952 if (manaShieldAbsorb > 0)
953 {
954 if (manaShieldAbsorb > dmgInfo.realDamage)
955 dmgInfo.realDamage = 0;
956 else
957 dmgInfo.realDamage -= manaShieldAbsorb;
958
959 dmgInfo.absorbedDamage += manaShieldAbsorb;
960 }
961
962 // Hackfix from legacy method
963 // Incanter's Absorption
964 if (victim->isPlayer())
965 {
966 uint32_t incanterSAbsorption[] =
967 {
968 //SPELL_HASH_INCANTER_S_ABSORPTION
969 44394,
970 44395,
971 44396,
972 44413,
973 0
974 };
975
976 if (victim->hasAurasWithId(incanterSAbsorption))
977 {
978 float_t pctmod = 0.0f;
979 const auto pl = static_cast<Player*>(victim);
980 if (pl->hasAurasWithId(44394))
981 pctmod = 0.05f;
982 else if (pl->hasAurasWithId(44395))
983 pctmod = 0.10f;
984 else if (pl->hasAurasWithId(44396))
985 pctmod = 0.15f;
986
987 const auto hp = static_cast<int32_t>(0.05f * pl->getMaxHealth());
988 auto spellpower = static_cast<int32_t>(pctmod * pl->getModDamageDonePositive(SCHOOL_NORMAL));
989
990 if (spellpower > hp)
991 spellpower = hp;
992
993 SpellInfo const* entry = sSpellMgr.getSpellInfo(44413);
994 SpellForcedBasePoints forcedBasePoints;
995 forcedBasePoints.set(0, spellpower);
996 if (entry != nullptr)
997 pl->castSpell(pl->getGuid(), entry, forcedBasePoints, true);
998 }
999 }
1000
1001 // Check for damage split target
1002 if (victim->m_damageSplitTarget != nullptr)
1003 dmgInfo.realDamage = victim->doDamageSplitTarget(dmgInfo.realDamage, dmgInfo.schoolMask, false);
1004
1005 // Get estimated overkill amount
1006 const auto overKill = victim->calculateEstimatedOverKillForCombatLog(dmgInfo.realDamage);
1007
1008 // Send packet
1009 if (isPeriodic && aurEff != nullptr && isCreatureOrPlayer())
1010 {
1011 const auto wasPacketSent = victim->sendPeriodicAuraLog(GetNewGUID(), victim->GetNewGUID(), spellInfo, dmgInfo.realDamage, overKill, dmgInfo.absorbedDamage, dmgInfo.resistedDamage, aurEff->getAuraEffectType(), dmgInfo.isCritical);
1012
1013 // In case periodic log couldn't be sent, send normal spell log
1014 // Required for leech and mana burn auras
1015 if (!wasPacketSent)
1016 victim->sendSpellNonMeleeDamageLog(this, victim, spellInfo, dmgInfo.realDamage, dmgInfo.absorbedDamage, dmgInfo.resistedDamage, 0, overKill, true, dmgInfo.isCritical);
1017 }
1018 else
1019 {
1020 victim->sendSpellNonMeleeDamageLog(this, victim, spellInfo, dmgInfo.realDamage, dmgInfo.absorbedDamage, dmgInfo.resistedDamage, 0, overKill, false, dmgInfo.isCritical);
1021 }
1022
1023 // Create damaging health batch event
1024 auto healthBatch = std::make_unique<HealthBatchEvent>();
1025 healthBatch->caster = dynamic_cast<Unit*>(this); // can be nullptr
1026 healthBatch->damageInfo = dmgInfo;
1027 healthBatch->isPeriodic = isPeriodic;
1028 healthBatch->spellInfo = spellInfo;
1029
1030 if (isLeech)
1031 {
1032 const uint8_t index = aur != nullptr && aurEff->getAuraEffectType() != SPELL_AURA_NONE ? aurEff->getEffectIndex() : effIndex;
1033 healthBatch->isLeech = true;
1034 healthBatch->leechMultipleValue = spellInfo->getEffectMultipleValue(index);
1035 }
1036
1037 victim->addHealthBatchEvent(std::move(healthBatch));
1038
1039 // Tagging should happen when damage packets are sent
1040 const auto plrOwner = getPlayerOwnerOrSelf();
1041 if (plrOwner != nullptr && victim->isCreature() && victim->isTaggableFor(ToUnit()))
1042 {
1043 victim->setTaggerGuid(ToUnit());
1044 plrOwner->tagUnit(victim);
1045 }
1046
1047 if (isCreatureOrPlayer())
1048 {
1049 const auto casterUnit = dynamic_cast<Unit*>(this);
1050 if (casterUnit != victim)
1051 {
1052 if (spell == nullptr && !isPeriodic)
1053 {
1054 // Send initial threat
1055 if (victim->isCreature())
1056 victim->getAIInterface()->onHostileAction(casterUnit);
1057
1058 // Handle combat for both caster and target
1059 casterUnit->getCombatHandler().onHostileAction(victim);
1060 victim->getCombatHandler().takeCombatAction(casterUnit);
1061 }
1062
1063 // Add real threat
1064 if (victim->getThreatManager().canHaveThreatList())
1065 {
1066 const auto threat = dmgInfo.realDamage == 0 ? 1 : dmgInfo.realDamage;
1067 const auto _spellInfo = spell != nullptr ? spell->getSpellInfo() : spellInfo;
1068 victim->getThreatManager().addThreat(casterUnit, static_cast<float>(threat), _spellInfo, false, false, spell);
1069 }
1070 }
1071
1072 // Handle procs
1073 victim->handleProc(dmgInfo.victimProcFlags, casterUnit, spellInfo, dmgInfo, isTriggered);
1074 // If called from spell class, handle caster's procs when spell has finished all targets
1075 if (spell == nullptr)
1076 casterUnit->handleProc(dmgInfo.attackerProcFlags, victim, spellInfo, dmgInfo, isTriggered);
1077 }
1078
1079 if (isPlayer())
1080 static_cast<Player*>(this)->m_castedAmount[school] = dmgInfo.realDamage;
1081
1082 // Cause push back to victim's spell casting if damage was not fully absorbed
1083 if (!(dmgInfo.realDamage == 0 && dmgInfo.absorbedDamage > 0) && !isPeriodic)
1084 {
1085 if (victim->getCurrentSpell(CURRENT_CHANNELED_SPELL) != nullptr && victim->getCurrentSpell(CURRENT_CHANNELED_SPELL)->getCastTimeLeft() > 0)
1086 victim->getCurrentSpell(CURRENT_CHANNELED_SPELL)->AddTime(school);
1087 else if (victim->getCurrentSpell(CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL) != nullptr && victim->getCurrentSpell(CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL)->getCastTimeLeft() > 0)
1088 victim->getCurrentSpell(CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL)->AddTime(school);
1089 }
1090
1091 // Creature emote on critical spell damage
1092 if (victim->isCreature() && !isPeriodic && dmgInfo.isCritical && dmgInfo.realDamage > 0)
1093 {
1094 const auto creatureTarget = static_cast<Creature*>(victim);
1095 if (creatureTarget->GetCreatureProperties()->Rank != ELITE_WORLDBOSS)
1096 creatureTarget->emote(EMOTE_ONESHOT_WOUNDCRITICAL);
1097 }
1098
1099 if (dmgInfo.resistedDamage == dmgInfo.realDamage && dmgInfo.absorbedDamage == 0)
1100 {
1101 // Hackfix from legacy method
1102 if (victim->isPlayer())
1103 {
1104 const auto pVictim = static_cast<Player*>(victim);
1105 if (pVictim->m_RegenManaOnSpellResist > 0)
1106 {
1107 const auto maxMana = pVictim->getMaxPower(POWER_TYPE_MANA);
1108 const auto amount = static_cast<uint32_t>(maxMana * pVictim->m_RegenManaOnSpellResist);
1109
1110 pVictim->energize(pVictim, 29442, amount, POWER_TYPE_MANA);
1111 }
1112 }
1113 }
1114
1115 // Hackfix from legacy method
1116 if (spellInfo->getSchoolMask() & SCHOOL_MASK_SHADOW)
1117 {
1118 if (victim->isAlive() && isCreatureOrPlayer())
1119 {
1120 //Shadow Word:Death
1121 if (spellId == 32379 || spellId == 32996 || spellId == 48157 || spellId == 48158)
1122 {
1123 auto backfireAmount = dmgInfo.realDamage + dmgInfo.absorbedDamage;
1124 static_cast<Unit*>(this)->addSimpleDamageBatchEvent(backfireAmount, static_cast<Unit*>(this), spellInfo);
1125 }
1126 }
1127 }
1128
1129 return dmgInfo;
1130}

1354 // If this is a direct heal spell just round the value
1355 dmgInfo.fullDamage = static_cast<int32_t>(std::round(heal));
1356 }
1357
1358 dmgInfo.realDamage = dmgInfo.fullDamage;
1359
1360 ///\ todo: implement absorbed heal (aura effect 301)
1361 dmgInfo.absorbedDamage = 0;
1362
1363 // Calculate estimated overheal amount
1364 const auto overHeal = victim->calculateEstimatedOverHealForCombatLog(dmgInfo.realDamage);
1365
1366 // Send packet
1367 if (isPeriodic && aurEff != nullptr && isCreatureOrPlayer())
1368 {
1369 const auto wasPacketSent = victim->sendPeriodicAuraLog(GetNewGUID(), victim->GetNewGUID(), spellInfo, dmgInfo.realDamage, overHeal, dmgInfo.absorbedDamage, 0, aurEff->getAuraEffectType(), dmgInfo.isCritical);
1370
1371 // In case periodic log couldn't be sent, send normal spell log
1372 // Required for leech auras
1373 if (!wasPacketSent)
1374 victim->sendSpellHealLog(this, victim, spellId, dmgInfo.realDamage, dmgInfo.isCritical, overHeal, dmgInfo.absorbedDamage);
1375 }
1376 else
1377 {
1378 victim->sendSpellHealLog(this, victim, spellId, dmgInfo.realDamage, dmgInfo.isCritical, overHeal, dmgInfo.absorbedDamage);
1379 }
1380
1381 // Create healing health batch
1382 auto healthBatch = std::make_unique<HealthBatchEvent>();
1383 healthBatch->caster = dynamic_cast<Unit*>(this); // can be nullptr
1384 healthBatch->damageInfo = dmgInfo;
1385 healthBatch->isPeriodic = isPeriodic;
1386 healthBatch->isHeal = true;
1387 healthBatch->spellInfo = spellInfo;
1388
1389 victim->addHealthBatchEvent(std::move(healthBatch));
1390
1391 if (isCreatureOrPlayer())
1392 {
1393 const auto casterUnit = dynamic_cast<Unit*>(this);
1394
1395 if (casterUnit != victim)
1396 {
1397 // Caster should enter combat if target is in combat
1398 // Periodic healing can also put caster in combat
1399 if (spell == nullptr)
1400 {
1401 casterUnit->getCombatHandler().onFriendlyAction(victim);
1402 victim->getCombatHandler().takeCombatAction(casterUnit, true);
1403 }
1404
1405 const auto _spellInfo = spell != nullptr ? spell->getSpellInfo() : spellInfo;
1406 victim->getThreatManager().forwardThreatForAssistingMe(casterUnit, static_cast<float_t>(dmgInfo.realDamage / 2), _spellInfo);
1407 }
1408
1409 // Handle procs
1410 victim->handleProc(dmgInfo.victimProcFlags, casterUnit, spellInfo, dmgInfo, isTriggered);
1411 // If called from spell class, handle caster's procs when spell has finished all targets
1412 if (spell == nullptr)
1413 casterUnit->handleProc(dmgInfo.attackerProcFlags, victim, spellInfo, dmgInfo, isTriggered);
1414 }
1415
1416 if (isPlayer())
1417 {
1418 const auto plr = static_cast<Player*>(this);
1419
1420 plr->m_lastHealSpell = spellInfo;
1421 plr->m_castedAmount[school] = dmgInfo.realDamage;
1422 }
1423
1424 victim->removeAurasByHeal();
1425 return dmgInfo;
1426}
1427
1428void Object::_UpdateSpells(uint32_t time)
1429{
1430 // Remove garbage
1431 removeGarbageSpells();
1432
1433 // Update autorepeat spells
1434 if (m_currentSpell[CURRENT_AUTOREPEAT_SPELL] != nullptr && isPlayer())
1435 static_cast<Player*>(this)->updateAutoRepeatSpell();
1436
1437 // Update traveling spells
1438 for (auto travelingSpellItr = m_travelingSpells.begin(); travelingSpellItr != m_travelingSpells.end();)
1439 {
1440 auto& spellItr = *travelingSpellItr;
1441
1442 // Remove finished spells from list
1443 // They will be deleted on next update tick
1444 if (spellItr.first == nullptr || spellItr.second)
1445 {
1446 addGarbageSpell(spellItr.first);
1447 travelingSpellItr = m_travelingSpells.erase(travelingSpellItr);
1448 continue;
1449 }
1450
1451 spellItr.first->update(time);
1452 ++travelingSpellItr;
1453 }
1454
1455 // Update current spells
1456 for (uint8_t i = 0; i < CURRENT_SPELL_MAX; ++i)
1457 {
1458 if (m_currentSpell[i] != nullptr)
1459 {
1460 // Remove finished spells from object's current spell array
1461 // If the spell is in finished state, it's already in garbage collector
1462 if (m_currentSpell[i]->getState() == SPELL_STATE_FINISHED)
1463 {
1464 m_currentSpell[i] = nullptr;
1465 }
1466 // Move traveling spells out from current spells
1467 else if (m_currentSpell[i]->getState() == SPELL_STATE_TRAVELING)
1468 {
1469 addTravelingSpell(m_currentSpell[i]);
1470 m_currentSpell[i] = nullptr;
1471 }
1472 // Update spells with other state
1473 else
1474 {
1475 m_currentSpell[i]->update(time);
1476 }
1477 }
1478 }
1479}

1490 (*itr).second = true;

1782void Object::BuildFieldUpdatePacket(Player* Target, uint32_t Index, uint32_t Value)
1783{
1784 ByteBuffer buf(500);
1785 buf << uint8_t(UPDATETYPE_VALUES);
1786#if VERSION_STRING < Mop
1787 buf << GetNewGUID();
1788#else
1789 buf.append(GetNewGUID());
1790#endif
1791
1792 uint32_t mBlocks = Index / 32 + 1;
1793 buf << uint8_t(mBlocks);
1794
1795 for (uint32_t dword_n = mBlocks - 1; dword_n; dword_n--)
1796 buf << uint32_t(0);
1797
1798 buf << (((uint32_t)(1)) << (Index % 32));
1799 buf << Value;
1800
1801 Target->getUpdateMgr().pushUpdateData(&buf, 1);
1802}

1817 *buf << uint32_t(0);
1818

1820 *buf << Value;
1821}

1823uint32_t Object::BuildValuesUpdateBlockForPlayer(ByteBuffer* data, Player* target)
1824{
1825 UpdateMask updateMask;
1826 updateMask.SetCount(m_valuesCount);
1827 setUpdateBits(&updateMask, target);
1828 for (uint32_t x = 0; x < m_valuesCount; ++x)
1829 {
1830 if (updateMask.GetBit(x))
1831 {
1832 if (m_wowGuid.GetNewGuidLen() > 0)
1833 {
1834 *data << uint8_t(UPDATETYPE_VALUES); // update type == update
1835 *data << m_wowGuid;
1836
1837 buildValuesUpdate(UPDATETYPE_VALUES, data, &updateMask, target);
1838#if VERSION_STRING == Mop
1839 * data << uint8_t(0);
1840#endif
1841 return 1;
1842 }
1843
1844 sLogger.failure("Object::BuildValuesUpdateBlockForPlayer tried to add data for invalid guid!");
1845 return 0;
1846 }
1847 }
1848
1849 return 0;
1850}

1862#if VERSION_STRING == Mop
1863 * buf << uint8_t(0);
1864#endif
1865 // 1 update.
1866 return 1;
1867 }

1869 sLogger.failure("Object::BuildValuesUpdateBlockForPlayer tried to add data for invalid guid!");
1870 return 0;

3079void Object::buildValuesUpdate(uint8_t updateType, ByteBuffer* data, UpdateMask* updateMask, Player* target)
3080{
3081 if (!updateMask)
3082 {
3083 sLogger.failure("Object::buildValuesUpdate invalid updateMask (nullptr)");
3084 return;
3085 }
3086
3087 if (isGameObject() && !isTransporter())
3088 {
3089#if VERSION_STRING < Mop
3090 updateMask->SetBit(getOffsetForStructuredField(WoWGameObject, dynamic));
3091#else
3092 updateMask->SetBit(getOffsetForStructuredField(WoWObject, dynamic_field));
3093#endif
3094
3095 if (updateType != UPDATETYPE_CREATE_OBJECT && updateType != UPDATETYPE_CREATE_OBJECT2)
3096 {
3097#if VERSION_STRING < WotLK
3098 updateMask->SetBit(getOffsetForStructuredField(WoWGameObject, animation_progress));
3099#elif VERSION_STRING < Mop
3100 updateMask->SetBit(getOffsetForStructuredField(WoWGameObject, bytes_1.bytes_1_gameobject.animation_progress));
3101#else
3102 updateMask->SetBit(getOffsetForStructuredField(WoWGameObject, bytes_2.bytes_2_gameobject.animation_progress));
3103#endif
3104 }
3105 }
3106
3107 if (updateMask->GetCount() != m_valuesCount)
3108 {
3109 sLogger.failure("Object::buildValuesUpdate values count in update mask is not equal to object values count!");
3110 return;
3111 }
3112
3113 uint32_t block_count, values_count;
3114 if (m_valuesCount > 2 * 0x20)
3115 {
3116 block_count = updateMask->GetUpdateBlockCount();
3117 values_count = std::min<uint32_t>(block_count * 0x20, m_valuesCount);
3118 }
3119 else
3120 {
3121 block_count = updateMask->GetBlockCount();
3122 values_count = m_valuesCount;
3123 }
3124
3125 *data << uint8_t(block_count);
3126 data->append(updateMask->GetMask(), block_count * 4);
3127
3128 for (uint32_t idx = 0; idx < values_count; ++idx)
3129 {
3130 if (updateMask->GetBit(idx))
3131 {
3132 // Some data must be altered because it has to be different to each player
3133 auto bitValue = m_uint32Values[idx];
3134
3135 if (target != nullptr)
3136 {
3137 if (isCreature())
3138 {
3139 auto* const creature = dynamic_cast<Creature*>(this);
3140
3141 if (idx == getOffsetForStructuredField(WoWUnit, unit_flags))
3142 {
3143 // Remove not selectable flag if GM mode is activated
3144 if (target->isGMFlagSet())
3145 bitValue &= ~UNIT_FLAG_NOT_SELECTABLE;
3146 }
3147 else if (idx == getOffsetForStructuredField(WoWUnit, display_id))
3148 {
3149 // Trigger npcs
3150 if (creature->GetCreatureProperties()->isTriggerNpc)
3151 {
3152 if (target->isGMFlagSet())
3153 bitValue = creature->GetCreatureProperties()->getVisibleModelForTriggerNpc();
3154 }
3155 }
3156#if VERSION_STRING < Mop
3157 else if (idx == getOffsetForStructuredField(WoWUnit, dynamic_flags))
3158#else
3159 else if (idx == getOffsetForStructuredField(WoWObject, dynamic_field))
3160#endif
3161 {
3162 auto dynamicFlags = bitValue & ~(U_DYN_FLAG_LOOTABLE | U_DYN_FLAG_TAGGED_BY_OTHER | U_DYN_FLAG_TAPPED_BY_PLAYER);
3163
3164 // Tagging
3165 if (creature->getTaggerGuid())
3166 {
3167 dynamicFlags |= U_DYN_FLAG_TAGGED_BY_OTHER;
3168
3169 if (creature->isTaggedByPlayerOrItsGroup(target))
3170 dynamicFlags |= U_DYN_FLAG_TAPPED_BY_PLAYER;
3171 }
3172
3173 // Loot
3174 if (!creature->loot.isLooted() && creature->HasLootForPlayer(target))
3175 dynamicFlags |= U_DYN_FLAG_LOOTABLE;
3176
3177 bitValue = dynamicFlags;
3178 }
3179 }
3180 else if (isGameObject())
3181 {
3182 auto* const gameobject = dynamic_cast<GameObject*>(this);
3183
3184#if VERSION_STRING < Mop
3185 if (idx == getOffsetForStructuredField(WoWGameObject, dynamic))
3186#else
3187 if (idx == getOffsetForStructuredField(WoWObject, dynamic_field))
3188#endif
3189 {
3190 union
3191 {
3192 struct
3193 {
3194 uint16_t dynamicFlags;
3195 int16_t pathProgress;
3196 } field_parts;
3197 uint32_t dynamicField;
3198 };
3199
3200 dynamicField = bitValue;
3201 field_parts.dynamicFlags &= ~(GO_DYN_FLAG_INTERACTABLE | GO_DYN_FLAG_SPARKLE);
3202
3203 if (!isTransporter())
3204 field_parts.pathProgress = 0;
3205
3206 const auto gobProperties = gameobject->GetGameObjectProperties();
3207
3208 // Loot
3209 if (!gobProperties->goMap.empty() || !gobProperties->itemMap.empty())
3210 {
3211 auto activeObject = false;
3212 for (const auto& questPair : gobProperties->goMap)
3213 {
3214 if (auto* const questLog = target->getQuestLogByQuestId(questPair.first->id))
3215 {
3216 const auto quest = questLog->getQuestProperties();
3217 if (quest->count_required_mob == 0)
3218 continue;
3219
3220 for (uint8_t i = 0; i < 4; ++i)
3221 {
3222 if (quest->required_mob_or_go[i] == static_cast<int32_t>(gameobject->getEntry()))
3223 {
3224 if (questLog->getMobCountByIndex(i) < quest->required_mob_or_go_count[i])
3225 {
3226 activeObject = true;
3227 break;
3228 }
3229 }
3230 }
3231 }
3232
3233 if (activeObject)
3234 break;
3235 }
3236
3237 if (!activeObject)
3238 {
3239 for (const auto& questItemData : gobProperties->itemMap)
3240 {
3241 for (const auto& itemPair : questItemData.second)
3242 {
3243 auto* const questLog = target->getQuestLogByQuestId(questItemData.first->id);
3244 if (questLog == nullptr)
3245 continue;
3246
3247 if (target->getItemInterface()->GetItemCount(itemPair.first) < itemPair.second)
3248 {
3249 activeObject = true;
3250 break;
3251 }
3252 }
3253
3254 if (activeObject)
3255 break;
3256 }
3257 }
3258
3259 if (activeObject)
3260 field_parts.dynamicFlags |= GO_DYN_FLAG_INTERACTABLE | GO_DYN_FLAG_SPARKLE;
3261 }
3262
3263 // Interactable gameobject
3264 if (!(field_parts.dynamicFlags & GO_DYN_FLAG_INTERACTABLE))
3265 {
3266 if (gameobject->isQuestGiver())
3267 {
3268 auto* const objectQuestGiver = dynamic_cast<GameObject_QuestGiver*>(this);
3269 if (objectQuestGiver->HasQuests())
3270 {
3271 auto activeObject = false;
3272 for (const auto& questRelation : objectQuestGiver->getQuestList())
3273 {
3274 if (questRelation == nullptr)
3275 continue;
3276
3277 const auto questProperties = questRelation->qst;
3278 if (questProperties == nullptr)
3279 continue;
3280
3281 // Activate object if player has not started the quest but only if player is also able to start quest
3282 // or if player has the quest and object is the quest ender
3283 if ((questRelation->type & QUESTGIVER_QUEST_START && !target->hasQuestInQuestLog(questProperties->id)
3284 && sQuestMgr.CalcQuestStatus(gameobject, target, questRelation.get()) >= QuestStatus::AvailableChat) ||
3285 (questRelation->type & QUESTGIVER_QUEST_END && target->hasQuestInQuestLog(questProperties->id)))
3286 {
3287 activeObject = true;
3288 break;
3289 }
3290 }
3291
3292 if (activeObject)
3293 field_parts.dynamicFlags |= GO_DYN_FLAG_INTERACTABLE;
3294 }
3295 }
3296 }
3297
3298 bitValue = dynamicField;
3299 }
3300 }
3301 else if (isCorpse())
3302 {
3303 auto* const corpse = dynamic_cast<Corpse*>(this);
3304
3305 if (idx == getOffsetForStructuredField(WoWCorpse, dynamic_flags))
3306 {
3307 auto dynamicFlags = bitValue & ~(U_DYN_FLAG_LOOTABLE | U_DYN_FLAG_TAPPED_BY_PLAYER);
3308
3309 // Loot
3310 // TODO: missing check if player is eligible to loot this corpse
3311 if (!corpse->loot.isLooted())
3312 dynamicFlags |= U_DYN_FLAG_LOOTABLE | U_DYN_FLAG_TAPPED_BY_PLAYER;
3313
3314 bitValue = dynamicFlags;
3315 }
3316 }
3317 }
3318
3319 *data << bitValue;
3320 }
3321 }

3354bool Object::SetPosition(float newX, float newY, float newZ, float newOrientation, [[maybe_unused]]bool allowPorting)
3355{
3356 bool updateMap = false, result = true;
3357
3358 if (!isValidMapCoord(newX, newY, newZ, newOrientation))
3359 return false;
3360
3361 if (!std::isnan(newX) && !std::isnan(newY) && !std::isnan(newOrientation))
3362 {
3363 //It's a good idea to push through EVERY transport position change, no matter how small they are. By: VLack aka. VLsoft
3364 if (isGameObject() && static_cast<GameObject*>(this)->GetGameObjectProperties()->type == GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_MO_TRANSPORT)
3365 updateMap = true;
3366
3367 //if (m_position.x != newX || m_position.y != newY)
3368 //updateMap = true;
3369 if (m_lastMapUpdatePosition.Distance2DSq({ newX, newY }) > 4.0f) /* 2.0f */
3370 updateMap = true;
3371
3372 m_position.ChangeCoords({ newX, newY, newZ, newOrientation });
3373
3374#if VERSION_STRING < Cata
3375 if (!allowPorting && newZ < -500)
3376 {
3377 m_position.z = 500;
3378 sLogger.failure("setPosition: fell through map; height ported");
3379
3380 result = false;
3381 }
3382#endif
3383
3384 if (IsInWorld() && updateMap)
3385 {
3386 m_lastMapUpdatePosition.ChangeCoords({ newX, newY, newZ, newOrientation });
3387 m_WorldMap->changeObjectLocation(this);
3388
3389 if (isPlayer() && dynamic_cast<Player*>(this)->getGroup() && dynamic_cast<Player*>(this)->getLastGroupPosition().Distance2DSq(m_position) > 25.0f) // distance of 5.0
3390 {
3391 dynamic_cast<Player*>(this)->addGroupUpdateFlag(GROUP_UPDATE_FLAG_POSITION);
3392 }
3393 }
3394
3395#ifdef FT_VEHICLES
3396 if (isCreatureOrPlayer())
3397 {
3398 if (ToUnit()->getVehicleKit() != nullptr)
3399 {
3400 ToUnit()->getVehicleKit()->relocatePassengers();
3401 }
3402 }
3403#endif
3404
3405 updatePositionData();
3406
3407 return result;
3408 }
3409
3410 sLogger.failure("Object::SetPosition one of the position values in NaN, returning false!");
3411 return false;

3660float Object::calcAngle(float Position1X, float Position1Y, float Position2X, float Position2Y)
3661{
3662 float dx = Position2X - Position1X;
3663 float dy = Position2Y - Position1Y;
3664 double angle = 0.0f;
3665
3666 // Calculate angle
3667 if (dx == 0.0)
3668 {
3669 if (dy == 0.0)
3670 angle = 0.0;
3671 else if (dy > 0.0)
3672 angle = M_PI * 0.5 /* / 2 */;
3673 else
3674 angle = M_PI * 3.0 * 0.5/* / 2 */;
3675 }
3676 else if (dy == 0.0)
3677 {
3678 if (dx > 0.0)
3679 angle = 0.0;
3680 else
3681 angle = M_PI;
3682 }
3683 else
3684 {
3685 if (dx < 0.0)
3686 angle = atanf(dy / dx) + M_PI;
3687 else if (dy < 0.0)
3688 angle = atanf(dy / dx) + (2 * M_PI);
3689 else
3690 angle = atanf(dy / dx);
3691 }
3692
3693 // Convert to degrees
3694 angle = angle * float(180 / M_PI);
3695
3696 // Return
3697 return float(angle);
3698}

3700float Object::calcRadAngle(float Position1X, float Position1Y, float Position2X, float Position2Y)
3701{
3702 double dx = double(Position2X - Position1X);
3703 double dy = double(Position2Y - Position1Y);
3704 double angle = 0.0;
3705
3706 // Calculate angle
3707 if (dx == 0.0)
3708 {
3709 if (dy == 0.0)
3710 angle = 0.0;
3711 else if (dy > 0.0)
3712 angle = M_PI * 0.5/*/ 2.0*/;
3713 else
3714 angle = M_PI * 3.0 * 0.5/*/ 2.0*/;
3715 }
3716 else if (dy == 0.0)
3717 {
3718 if (dx > 0.0)
3719 angle = 0.0;
3720 else
3721 angle = M_PI;
3722 }
3723 else
3724 {
3725 if (dx < 0.0)
3726 angle = atan(dy / dx) + M_PI;
3727 else if (dy < 0.0)
3728 angle = atan(dy / dx) + (2 * M_PI);
3729 else
3730 angle = atan(dy / dx);
3731 }
3732
3733 // Return
3734 return float(angle);

3750bool Object::inArc(float Position1X, float Position1Y, float FOV, float Orientation, float Position2X, float Position2Y)
3751{

3756 if (((angle >= lborder) && (angle <= rborder)) || ((lborder > rborder) && ((angle < rborder) || (angle > lborder))))
3757 {
3758 return true;

3760 else
3761 {
3762 return false;

3766bool Object::isInFront(Object* target)
3767{
3768 // check if we facing something (is the object within a 180 degree slice of our positive y axis)
3769
3770 double x = target->GetPositionX() - m_position.x;
3771 double y = target->GetPositionY() - m_position.y;
3772
3773 double angle = atan2(y, x);
3774 angle = (angle >= 0.0) ? angle : 2.0 * M_PI + angle;
3775 angle -= m_position.o;
3776
3777 while (angle > M_PI)
3778 angle -= 2.0 * M_PI;
3779
3780 while (angle < -M_PI)
3781 angle += 2.0 * M_PI;
3782
3783 // replace M_PI in the two lines below to reduce or increase angle
3784
3785 double left = -1.0 * (M_PI / 2.0);
3786 double right = (M_PI / 2.0);
3787
3788 return((angle >= left) && (angle <= right));
3789}
3790
3791bool Object::isInBack(Object* target)
3792{
3793 // check if we are behind something (is the object within a 180 degree slice of our negative y axis)
3794
3795 double x = m_position.x - target->GetPositionX();
3796 double y = m_position.y - target->GetPositionY();
3797
3798 double angle = atan2(y, x);
3799 angle = (angle >= 0.0) ? angle : 2.0 * M_PI + angle;
3800
3801 // if we are a creature and have a UNIT_FIELD_TARGET then we are always facing them
3802 if (isCreature() && static_cast<Creature*>(this)->getTargetGuid() != 0)
3803 {
3804 Unit* pTarget = static_cast<Creature*>(this)->getAIInterface()->getCurrentTarget();
3805 if (pTarget != nullptr)
3806 angle -= double(Object::calcRadAngle(target->m_position.x, target->m_position.y, pTarget->m_position.x, pTarget->m_position.y));
3807 else
3808 angle -= target->GetOrientation();
3809 }
3810 else
3811 angle -= target->GetOrientation();
3812
3813 while (angle > M_PI)
3814 angle -= 2.0 * M_PI;
3815
3816 while (angle < -M_PI)
3817 angle += 2.0 * M_PI;
3818
3819 // replace M_H_PI in the two lines below to reduce or increase angle
3820
3821 double left = -1.0 * (M_H_PI / 2.0);
3822 double right = (M_H_PI / 2.0);
3823
3824 return((angle <= left) && (angle >= right));
3825}

3885Standing Object::getEnemyReaction(Object* target)
3886{
3887 // always friendly to self
3888 if (this == target)
3889 return Standing::STANDING_FRIENDLY;
3890
3891 // always friendly to charmer or owner
3892 if (getUnitOwnerOrSelf() == target->getUnitOwnerOrSelf())
3893 return Standing::STANDING_FRIENDLY;
3894
3895 Player* selfPlayerOwner = getPlayerOwnerOrSelf();
3896 Player* targetPlayerOwner = target->getPlayerOwnerOrSelf();
3897
3898 // check forced reputation
3899 // which could be applied by spell auras
3900 if (selfPlayerOwner)
3901 {
3902 if (WDB::Structures::FactionTemplateEntry const* targetFactionTemplateEntry = target->m_factionTemplate)
3903 if (Standing const* repRank = selfPlayerOwner->getForcedReputationRank(targetFactionTemplateEntry))
3904 return *repRank;
3905 }
3906 else if (targetPlayerOwner)
3907 {
3908 if (WDB::Structures::FactionTemplateEntry const* selfFactionTemplateEntry = m_factionTemplate)
3909 if (Standing const* repRank = targetPlayerOwner->getForcedReputationRank(selfFactionTemplateEntry))
3910 return *repRank;
3911 }
3912
3913 Unit* unit = ToUnit() ? ToUnit() : selfPlayerOwner;
3914 Unit* targetUnit = target->ToUnit() ? target->ToUnit() : targetPlayerOwner;
3915 if (unit && unit->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_PVP_ATTACKABLE))
3916 {
3917 if (targetUnit && targetUnit->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_PVP_ATTACKABLE))
3918 {
3919 if (selfPlayerOwner && targetPlayerOwner)
3920 {
3921 // always friendly to other unit controlled by player, or to the player himself
3922 if (selfPlayerOwner == targetPlayerOwner)
3923 return STANDING_FRIENDLY;
3924
3925 // Sanctuary
3926 if (selfPlayerOwner->isSanctuaryFlagSet())
3927 return STANDING_FRIENDLY;
3928
3929 // Duelling
3930 if ((selfPlayerOwner->getDuelPlayer() == targetPlayerOwner) && (selfPlayerOwner->getDuelState() == DUEL_STATE_STARTED))
3931 return STANDING_HOSTILE;
3932
3933 // Same Group
3934 if (selfPlayerOwner->getGroup() && selfPlayerOwner->getGroup() == targetPlayerOwner->getGroup())
3935 return STANDING_FRIENDLY;
3936 }
3937
3938 // check Free for all PVP
3939 if (unit->isFfaPvpFlagSet() && targetUnit->isFfaPvpFlagSet())
3940 return STANDING_HOSTILE;
3941
3942 if (selfPlayerOwner)
3943 {
3944 if (WDB::Structures::FactionTemplateEntry const* targetFactionTemplateEntry = targetUnit->m_factionTemplate)
3945 {
3946 if (Standing const* repRank = selfPlayerOwner->getForcedReputationRank(targetFactionTemplateEntry))
3947 return *repRank;
3948
3949#if VERSION_STRING > Classic
3950 if (!selfPlayerOwner->hasUnitFlags2(UNIT_FLAG2_UNK2))
3951 {
3952 if (WDB::Structures::FactionEntry const* targetFactionEntry = sFactionStore.lookupEntry(targetFactionTemplateEntry->Faction))
3953 {
3954 if (targetFactionEntry->canHaveReputation())
3955 {
3956 // check contested flags
3957 if ((targetUnit->m_factionTemplate->FactionGroup & FACTION_TEMPLATE_FLAG_CONTESTED_GUARD) &&
3958 selfPlayerOwner->hasPlayerFlags(PLAYER_FLAG_PVP_GUARD_ATTACKABLE))
3959 return STANDING_HOSTILE;
3960
3961 // if faction has reputation its reaction depends on our war state
3962 if (selfPlayerOwner->isFactionAtWar(targetUnit->m_factionEntry))
3963 return STANDING_HOSTILE;
3964
3965 return STANDING_FRIENDLY;
3966 }
3967 }
3968 }
3969#endif
3970 }
3971 }
3972 }
3973 }
3974
3975 // do checks dependant only on our faction
3976 return getFactionReaction(m_factionTemplate, target);
3977}
3978
3979Standing Object::getFactionReaction(WDB::Structures::FactionTemplateEntry const* factionTemplateEntry, Object* target)
3980{
3981 // always neutral when no template entry found
3982 if (!factionTemplateEntry)
3983 return STANDING_NEUTRAL;
3984
3985 WDB::Structures::FactionTemplateEntry const* targetFactionTemplateEntry = target->m_factionTemplate;
3986 if (!targetFactionTemplateEntry)
3987 return STANDING_NEUTRAL;
3988
3989 if (Player* targetPlayerOwner = target->getPlayerOwnerOrSelf())
3990 {
3991 // check contested flags
3992 if ((factionTemplateEntry->FactionGroup & FACTION_TEMPLATE_FLAG_CONTESTED_GUARD) &&
3993 targetPlayerOwner->hasPlayerFlags(PLAYER_FLAG_PVP_GUARD_ATTACKABLE))
3994 return STANDING_HOSTILE;
3995
3996 if (Standing const* repRank = targetPlayerOwner->getForcedReputationRank(factionTemplateEntry))
3997 return *repRank;
3998
3999#if VERSION_STRING > Classic
4000 if (target->ToUnit() && !target->ToUnit()->hasUnitFlags2(UNIT_FLAG2_UNK2))
4001#else
4002 if (target->ToUnit())
4003#endif
4004 {
4005 if (WDB::Structures::FactionEntry const* factionEntry = sFactionStore.lookupEntry(factionTemplateEntry->Faction))
4006 {
4007 if (factionEntry->canHaveReputation())
4008 {
4009 Standing repRank = targetPlayerOwner->getFactionStandingRank(factionEntry->ID);
4010 if (targetPlayerOwner->isFactionAtWar(factionEntry))
4011 repRank = std::min(STANDING_NEUTRAL, repRank);
4012 return repRank;
4013 }
4014 }
4015 }
4016 }
4017
4018 // common faction based check
4019 if (factionTemplateEntry->isHostileTo(*targetFactionTemplateEntry))
4020 return STANDING_HOSTILE;
4021 if (factionTemplateEntry->isFriendlyTo(*targetFactionTemplateEntry))
4022 return STANDING_FRIENDLY;
4023 if (targetFactionTemplateEntry->isFriendlyTo(*factionTemplateEntry))
4024 return STANDING_FRIENDLY;
4025 if (factionTemplateEntry->FactionGroup & FACTION_TEMPLATE_FLAG_HOSTILE_BY_DEFAULT)
4026 return STANDING_HOSTILE;
4027 // neutral by default
4028 return STANDING_NEUTRAL;
4029}

4072
4073bool Object::isValidTarget(Object* target, SpellInfo const* bySpell)
4074{
4075 if (!this)
4076 return false;
4077
4078 if (!target)
4079 return false;
4080
4081 // some positive spells can be casted at hostile target
4082 bool isPositiveSpell = bySpell && !bySpell->isNegativeAura();
4083
4084 // can't attack self (spells can, attribute check)
4085 if (!bySpell && this == target)
4086 return false;
4087
4088 // can't attack unattackable units
4089 Unit* unitTarget = target->ToUnit();
4090 if (unitTarget && unitTarget->hasUnitStateFlag(UNIT_STATE_UNATTACKABLE))
4091 return false;
4092
4093 // can't attack GMs
4094 if (target->isPlayer() && target->ToPlayer()->isGMFlagSet())
4095 return false;
4096
4097 // Creature should not attack permanently invisible units
4098 Unit* unit = ToUnit();
4099 if (unit)
4100 {
4101 // can't attack invisible
4102 if (!bySpell || !bySpell->hasAttribute(ATTRIBUTESEXF_CAN_TARGET_INVISIBLE))
4103 {
4104 if (unit->getInvisibilityLevel(INVIS_FLAG_NEVER_VISIBLE) > 0)
4105 return false;
4106
4107 // can't attack invisible
4108 if (!unit->canSee(target))
4109 return false;
4110 }
4111 }
4112
4113 // can't attack dead
4114 if ((!bySpell || !bySpell->isAllowingDeadTarget()) && unitTarget && !unitTarget->isAlive())
4115 return false;
4116
4117 // can't attack untargetable
4118 if ((!bySpell || !bySpell->hasAttribute(ATTRIBUTESEXF_UNK26)) && unitTarget && unitTarget->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_NOT_SELECTABLE))
4119 return false;
4120
4121#if VERSION_STRING >= TBC
4122 if (Player const* playerAttacker = ToPlayer())
4123 {
4124 if (playerAttacker->hasPlayerFlags(PLAYER_FLAG_UNK20))
4125 return false;
4126 }
4127#endif
4128
4129 // check flags
4130 if (unitTarget && unitTarget->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_NON_ATTACKABLE | UNIT_FLAG_MOUNTED_TAXI | UNIT_FLAG_IGNORE_CREATURE_COMBAT | UNIT_FLAG_ALIVE))
4131 return false;
4132
4133 Unit* unitOrOwner = unit;
4134 GameObject* go = ToGameObject();
4135 if (go && go->getGoType() == GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_TRAP)
4136 unitOrOwner = static_cast<GameObject_Trap*>(go)->getUnitOwner();
4137
4138 // ignore immunity flags when assisting
4139 if (unitOrOwner && unitTarget && !(isPositiveSpell && bySpell->hasAttribute(ATTRIBUTESEXF_UNK5)))
4140 {
4141 if (!unitOrOwner->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_PVP_ATTACKABLE) && unitTarget->getAIInterface()->isIgnoringCreatureCombat())
4142 return false;
4143
4144 if (!unitTarget->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_PVP_ATTACKABLE) && unitOrOwner->getAIInterface()->isIgnoringCreatureCombat())
4145 return false;
4146
4147 if (unitOrOwner->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_PVP_ATTACKABLE) && unitTarget->getAIInterface()->isIgnoringPlayerCombat())
4148 return false;
4149
4150 if (unitTarget->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_PVP_ATTACKABLE) && unitOrOwner->getAIInterface()->isIgnoringPlayerCombat())
4151 return false;
4152 }
4153
4154 // Creature Vs Creature
4155 if (unit&& !unit->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_PVP_ATTACKABLE) && unitTarget && !unitTarget->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_PVP_ATTACKABLE))
4156 return isHostileTo(unitTarget) || unitTarget->isHostileTo(this);
4157
4158 // Traps without owner or with NPC owner versus Creature case - can attack to creature only when one of them is hostile
4159 if (go && go->getGoType() == GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_TRAP)
4160 {
4161 Unit const* goOwner = static_cast<GameObject_Trap*>(go)->getUnitOwner();
4162 if (!goOwner || !goOwner->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_PVP_ATTACKABLE))
4163 if (unitTarget && !unitTarget->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_PVP_ATTACKABLE))
4164 return isHostileTo(unitTarget) || unitTarget->isHostileTo(this);
4165 }
4166
4167 // Player vs Player, Player vs Creature, Creature vs Player case
4168 // can't attack friendly targets
4169 if (isFriendlyTo(target) || target->isFriendlyTo(this))
4170 return false;
4171
4172 Player* playerAffectingAttacker = unit && unit->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_PVP_ATTACKABLE) ? getPlayerOwnerOrSelf() : go ? getPlayerOwner() : nullptr;
4173 Player* playerAffectingTarget = unitTarget && unitTarget->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_PVP_ATTACKABLE) ? unitTarget->getPlayerOwnerOrSelf() : nullptr;
4174
4175 // Not all neutral creatures can be attacked (even some unfriendly faction does not react aggresive to you, like Sporaggar)
4176 if ((playerAffectingAttacker && !playerAffectingTarget) || (!playerAffectingAttacker && playerAffectingTarget))
4177 {
4178 Player* player = playerAffectingAttacker ? playerAffectingAttacker : playerAffectingTarget;
4179
4180 if (Unit* creature = playerAffectingAttacker ? unitTarget : unit)
4181 {
4182 if (creature->getAIInterface()->isGuard() && player->hasPlayerFlags(PLAYER_FLAG_PVP_GUARD_ATTACKABLE))
4183 return true;
4184
4185 if (WDB::Structures::FactionTemplateEntry const* factionTemplate = creature->m_factionTemplate)
4186 {
4187 if (!(player->getForcedReputationRank(factionTemplate)))
4188 if (WDB::Structures::FactionEntry const* factionEntry = sFactionStore.lookupEntry(factionTemplate->Faction))
4189 if (player->isHostileBasedOnReputation(factionEntry))
4190 return false;
4191 }
4192 }
4193 }
4194
4195 Creature* creatureAttacker = ToCreature();
4196 if (creatureAttacker && (creatureAttacker->GetCreatureProperties()->typeFlags & CREATURE_FLAG1_PARTY_MEMBER))
4197 return false;
4198
4199 if (playerAffectingAttacker && playerAffectingTarget)
4200 if (playerAffectingAttacker->getDuelPlayer() == playerAffectingTarget && playerAffectingAttacker->getDuelState() == DUEL_STATE_STARTED)
4201 return true;
4202
4203 // PvP case - can't attack when attacker or target are in sanctuary
4204 if (unitTarget && unitTarget->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_PVP_ATTACKABLE) && unitOrOwner && unitOrOwner->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_PVP_ATTACKABLE) && (unitTarget->isSanctuaryFlagSet() || unitOrOwner->isSanctuaryFlagSet()))
4205 return false;
4206
4207 // additional checks - only PvP case
4208 if (playerAffectingAttacker && playerAffectingTarget)
4209 {
4210 if (playerAffectingTarget->isPvpFlagSet())
4211 return true;
4212
4213 if (playerAffectingAttacker->isFfaPvpFlagSet() && playerAffectingTarget->isFfaPvpFlagSet())
4214 return true;
4215 }
4216
4217 return true;
4218}
4219
4220bool Object::isValidAssistTarget(Unit* target, SpellInfo const* bySpell)
4221{
4222 // can assist to self
4223 if (this == target)
4224 return true;
4225
4226 // some positive spells can be casted at hostile target
4227 bool isNegativeSpell = bySpell && bySpell->isNegativeAura();
4228
4229 // can assist to self
4230 if (target == nullptr)
4231 return false;
4232
4233 // can't assist unattackable units
4234 Unit* unitTarget = target->ToUnit();
4235 if (unitTarget && unitTarget->hasUnitStateFlag(UNIT_STATE_UNATTACKABLE))
4236 return false;
4237
4238 // can't assist GMs
4239 if (target->isPlayer() && target->ToPlayer()->isGMFlagSet())
4240 return false;
4241
4242 // Creature should not assist permanently invisible units
4243 if (target->getInvisibilityLevel(INVIS_FLAG_NEVER_VISIBLE) > 0)
4244 return false;
4245
4246 Unit* unit = ToUnit();
4247#ifdef FT_VEHICLES
4248 // can't assist own vehicle or passenger
4249 if (unit && unitTarget && unit->getVehicle())
4250 {
4251 if (unit->isOnVehicle(target))
4252 return false;
4253
4254 if (unit->getVehicleBase()->isOnVehicle(unitTarget))
4255 return false;
4256 }
4257#endif
4258
4259 // can't assist invisible
4260 if (!bySpell || !bySpell->hasAttribute(ATTRIBUTESEXF_CAN_TARGET_INVISIBLE))
4261 {
4262 if (unit->getInvisibilityLevel(INVIS_FLAG_NEVER_VISIBLE) > 0)
4263 return false;
4264
4265 // can't attack invisible
4266 if (!unit->canSee(target))
4267 return false;
4268 }
4269
4270 // can't assist dead
4271 if ((!bySpell || !bySpell->isAllowingDeadTarget()) && unitTarget && !unitTarget->isAlive())
4272 return false;
4273
4274 // can't assist untargetable
4275 if ((!bySpell || !bySpell->hasAttribute(ATTRIBUTESEXF_UNK26)) && unitTarget && unitTarget->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_NOT_SELECTABLE))
4276 return false;
4277
4278 // check flags for negative spells
4279 if (isNegativeSpell && unitTarget && unitTarget->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_NON_ATTACKABLE | UNIT_FLAG_MOUNTED_TAXI | UNIT_FLAG_IGNORE_CREATURE_COMBAT | UNIT_FLAG_ALIVE))
4280 return false;
4281
4282
4283 if (isNegativeSpell || !bySpell || !bySpell->hasAttribute(ATTRIBUTESEXF_UNK5))
4284 {
4285 if (unit && unit->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_PVP_ATTACKABLE))
4286 {
4287 if (unitTarget->getAIInterface()->isIgnoringPlayerCombat())
4288 return false;
4289 }
4290 else
4291 {
4292 if (unitTarget->getAIInterface()->isIgnoringCreatureCombat())
4293 return false;
4294 }
4295 }
4296
4297 // can't assist non-friendly targets
4298 if (getEnemyReaction(target) < STANDING_NEUTRAL && target->getEnemyReaction(this) < STANDING_NEUTRAL && (!ToCreature() || !(ToCreature()->GetCreatureProperties()->typeFlags & CREATURE_FLAG1_PARTY_MEMBER)))
4299 return false;
4300
4301 // PvP case
4302 if (unitTarget && unitTarget->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_PVP_ATTACKABLE))
4303 {
4304 if (unit && unit->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_PVP_ATTACKABLE))
4305 {
4306 Player const* selfPlayerOwner = getPlayerOwnerOrSelf();
4307 Player const* targetPlayerOwner = unitTarget->getPlayerOwnerOrSelf();
4308 if (selfPlayerOwner && targetPlayerOwner)
4309 {
4310 // can't assist player which is dueling someone
4311 if (selfPlayerOwner != targetPlayerOwner && targetPlayerOwner->getDuelPlayer())
4312 return false;
4313 }
4314 // can't assist player in ffa_pvp zone from outside
4315 if (unitTarget->isFfaPvpFlagSet() && !unit->isFfaPvpFlagSet())
4316 return false;
4317
4318 // can't assist player out of sanctuary from sanctuary if has pvp enabled
4319 if (unitTarget->isPvpFlagSet())
4320 if (unit->isSanctuaryFlagSet() && !unitTarget->isSanctuaryFlagSet())
4321 return false;
4322 }
4323 }
4324 // PvC case - player can assist creature only if has specific type flags
4325 else if (unit && unit->hasUnitFlags(UNIT_FLAG_PVP_ATTACKABLE))
4326 {
4327 if (!bySpell || !bySpell->hasAttribute(ATTRIBUTESEXF_UNK5))
4328 if (!target->isPvpFlagSet())
4329 if (Creature* creatureTarget = target->ToCreature())
4330 return ((creatureTarget->GetCreatureProperties()->typeFlags & CREATURE_FLAG1_PARTY_MEMBER) || (creatureTarget->GetCreatureProperties()->typeFlags & CREATURE_FLAG1_AID_PLAYERS));
4331 }
4332
4333 return true;
4334}

4460 break;

4518void Object::SendCreatureChatMessageInRange(Creature* creature, uint32_t textId, Unit* target/* = nullptr*/)
4519{
4520 uint32_t myphase = GetPhase();
4521 std::shared_lock<std::shared_mutex> playerLock(m_inRangePlayerSetMutex);
4522 for (const auto& itr : mInRangePlayersSet)

4524 Object* object = itr;

4526 {

4529 Player* player = static_cast<Player*>(object);
4530 uint32_t sessionLanguage = player->getSession()->language;
4531

4543 else
4544 message = npcScriptText->text;
4545
4546 if (npcScriptText->emote != 0)
4547 creature->eventAddEmote((EmoteType)npcScriptText->emote, npcScriptText->duration);
4548
4549 if (npcScriptText->sound != 0)
4550 creature->PlaySoundToSet(npcScriptText->sound);
4551
4552 const auto data = creature->createChatPacket(npcScriptText->type, npcScriptText->language, message, target, sessionLanguage);
4553 player->sendPacket(data.get());
4554 }
4555 }
4556 }

4661bool Object::GetPoint(float angle, float rad, float & outx, float & outy, float & outz, bool sloppypath)
4662{
4663 if (!IsInWorld())
4664 return false;
4665 outx = GetPositionX() + rad * cos(angle);
4666 outy = GetPositionY() + rad * sin(angle);
4667 outz = getWorldMap()->getHeight(LocationVector(outx, outy, GetPositionZ() + 2));
4668
4669 float waterz = getWorldMap()->getWaterLevel(outx, outy);
4670
4671 outz = std::max(waterz, outz);
4672
4673 MMAP::MMapManager* mmap = MMAP::MMapFactory::createOrGetMMapManager();
4674 dtNavMesh* nav = const_cast<dtNavMesh*>(mmap->GetNavMesh(GetMapId()));
4675 dtNavMeshQuery* nav_query = const_cast<dtNavMeshQuery*>(mmap->GetNavMeshQuery(GetMapId(), GetInstanceID()));
4676 //NavMeshData* nav = CollideInterface.GetNavMesh(GetMapId());
4677
4678 if (nav != nullptr)
4679 {
4680 //if we can path there, go for it
4681 if (!isCreatureOrPlayer() || !sloppypath /*|| !static_cast<Unit*>(this)->getAIInterface()->CanCreatePath(outx, outy, outz)*/)
4682 {
4683 //raycast nav mesh to see if this place is valid
4684 float start[3] = { GetPositionY(), GetPositionZ() + 0.5f, GetPositionX() };
4685 float end[3] = { outy, outz + 0.5f, outx };
4686 float extents[3] = { 3, 5, 3 };
4687 dtQueryFilter filter;
4688 filter.setIncludeFlags(NAV_GROUND | NAV_WATER | NAV_MAGMA_SLIME);
4689
4690 dtPolyRef startref;
4691 nav_query->findNearestPoly(start, extents, &filter, &startref, nullptr);
4692
4693 float point;
4694 float hitNormal[3];
4695 float result[3];
4696 int numvisited;
4697 dtPolyRef visited[MAX_PATH_LENGTH];
4698
4699 dtStatus rayresult = nav_query->raycast(startref, start, end, &filter, &point, hitNormal, visited, &numvisited, MAX_PATH_LENGTH);
4700
4701 if (point <= 1.0f)
4702 {
4703 if (numvisited == 0 || rayresult == DT_FAILURE)
4704 {
4705 result[0] = start[0];
4706 result[1] = start[1];
4707 result[2] = start[2];
4708 }
4709 else
4710 {
4711 result[0] = start[0] + ((end[0] - start[0]) * point);
4712 result[1] = start[1] + ((end[1] - start[1]) * point);
4713 result[2] = start[2] + ((end[2] - start[2]) * point);
4714 nav_query->getPolyHeight(visited[numvisited - 1], result, &result[1]);
4715 }
4716
4717 //copy end back to function floats
4718 outy = result[0];
4719 outz = result[1];
4720 outx = result[2];
4721 }
4722 }
4723 }
4724 else //test against vmap if mmap isn't available
4725 {
4726 float testx, testy, testz;
4727
4728 const auto mgr = VMAP::VMapFactory::createOrGetVMapManager();
4729 bool isHittingObject = mgr->getObjectHitPos(GetMapId(), GetPositionX(), GetPositionY(), GetPositionZ() + 2, outx, outy, outz + 2, testx, testy, testz, -0.5f);
4730
4731 if (isHittingObject)
4732 {
4733 //hit something
4734 outx = testx;
4735 outy = testy;
4736 outz = testz;
4737 }
4738
4739 outz = getMapHeight(LocationVector(outx, outy, outz + 2));
4740 }
4741
4742 return true;
4743}
4744
4745void Object::getNearPoint2D(Object* searcher, float& x, float& y, float distance2d, float absAngle)
4746{
4747 float effectiveReach = getCombatReach();
4748
4749 if (searcher)
4750 {
4751 effectiveReach += searcher->getCombatReach();
4752
4753#if VERSION_STRING >= WotLK
4754 if (this != searcher)
4755 {
4756 float myHover = 0.0f, searcherHover = 0.0f;
4757 if (Unit const* unit = ToUnit())
4758 myHover = unit->getHoverHeight();
4759 if (Unit const* searchUnit = searcher->ToUnit())
4760 searcherHover = searchUnit->getHoverHeight();
4761
4762 float hoverDelta = myHover - searcherHover;
4763 if (hoverDelta != 0.0f)
4764 effectiveReach = std::sqrt(std::max(effectiveReach * effectiveReach - hoverDelta * hoverDelta, 0.0f));
4765 }
4766#endif
4767 }
4768
4769 x = GetPositionX() + (effectiveReach + distance2d) * std::cos(absAngle);
4770 y = GetPositionY() + (effectiveReach + distance2d) * std::sin(absAngle);
4771}
4772
4773void Object::getNearPoint(Object* searcher, float& x, float& y, float& z, float distance2d, float absAngle)
4774{
4775 getNearPoint2D(searcher, x, y, distance2d, absAngle);
4776 z = GetPositionZ();
4777 (searcher ? searcher : this)->updateAllowedPositionZ(x, y, z);
4778
4779 // if detection disabled, return first point
4780 if (!worldConfig.terrainCollision.isCollisionEnabled)
4781 return;
4782
4783 // return if the point is already in LoS
4784 if (IsWithinLOS(LocationVector(x, y, z)))
4785 return;
4786
4787 // remember first point
4788 float first_x = x;
4789 float first_y = y;
4790 float first_z = z;
4791
4792 // loop in a circle to look for a point in LoS using small steps
4793 for (float angle = float(M_PI) / 8; angle < float(M_PI) * 2; angle += float(M_PI) / 8)
4794 {
4795 getNearPoint2D(searcher, x, y, distance2d, absAngle + angle);
4796 z = GetPositionZ();
4797 (searcher ? searcher : this)->updateAllowedPositionZ(x, y, z);
4798 if (IsWithinLOS(LocationVector(x,y,z)))
4799 return;
4800 }
4801
4802 // still not in LoS, give up and return first position found
4803 x = first_x;
4804 y = first_y;
4805 z = first_z;
4806
4807 normalizeMapCoord(x);
4808 normalizeMapCoord(y);
4809}

4854void Object::updateAllowedPositionZ(float x, float y, float &z, float* groundZ)
4855{
4856 // TODO: Allow transports to be part of dynamic vmap tree
4857 if (GetTransport())
4858 {
4859 if (groundZ)
4860 *groundZ = z + 1.0f; // dont clip inside our transport :)
4861
4862 return;
4863 }
4864
4865 if (Unit* unit = ToUnit())
4866 {
4867 if (!unit->canFly())
4868 {
4869 bool canSwim = unit->canSwim();
4870 float ground_z = z;
4871 float max_z;
4872 if (canSwim)
4873 max_z = getMapWaterOrGroundLevel(x, y, z, &ground_z);
4874 else
4875 max_z = ground_z = getMapHeight(LocationVector(x, y, z));
4876
4877 if (max_z > INVALID_HEIGHT)
4878 {
4879#if VERSION_STRING >= WotLK
4880 // hovering units cannot go below their hover height
4881 float hoverOffset = unit->getHoverHeight();
4882 max_z += hoverOffset;
4883 ground_z += hoverOffset;
4884#endif
4885
4886 if (z > max_z)
4887 z = max_z;
4888 else if (z < ground_z)
4889 z = ground_z;
4890 }
4891
4892 if (groundZ)
4893 *groundZ = ground_z;
4894 }
4895 else
4896 {
4897 float ground_z = getMapHeight(LocationVector(x, y, z));
4898#if VERSION_STRING >= WotLK
4899 ground_z += unit->getHoverHeight();
4900#endif
4901
4902 if (z < ground_z)
4903 z = ground_z;
4904
4905 if (groundZ)
4906 *groundZ = ground_z;
4907 }
4908 }
4909 else
4910 {
4911 float ground_z = getMapHeight(LocationVector(x, y, z));
4912 if (ground_z > INVALID_HEIGHT)
4913 z = ground_z;
4914
4915 if (groundZ)
4916 *groundZ = ground_z;
4917 }
4918}

4926
4927void Object::movePositionToFirstCollision(LocationVector &pos, float dist, float angle)
4928{
4929 angle += GetOrientation();
4930 float destx, desty, destz;
4931 destx = pos.x + dist * std::cos(angle);
4932 desty = pos.y + dist * std::sin(angle);
4933 destz = pos.z;
4934
4935 // Use a detour raycast to get our first collision point
4936 PathGenerator path(this);
4937 path.setUseRaycast(true);
4938 path.calculatePath(destx, desty, destz, false);
4939
4940 // Check for valid path types before we proceed
4941 if (!(path.getPathType() & PATHFIND_NOT_USING_PATH))
4942 if (path.getPathType() & ~(PATHFIND_NORMAL | PATHFIND_SHORTCUT | PATHFIND_INCOMPLETE | PATHFIND_FARFROMPOLY_END))
4943 return;
4944
4945 G3D::Vector3 result = path.getPath().back();
4946 destx = result.x;
4947 desty = result.y;
4948 destz = result.z;
4949
4950 // check static LOS
4951 float halfHeight = getCollisionHeight() * 0.5f;
4952 bool col = false;
4953
4954 // Unit is flying, check for potential collision via vmaps
4955 if (path.getPathType() & PATHFIND_NOT_USING_PATH)
4956 {
4957 col = VMAP::VMapFactory::createOrGetVMapManager()->getObjectHitPos(GetMapId(),
4958 pos.x, pos.y, pos.z + halfHeight,
4959 destx, desty, destz + halfHeight,
4960 destx, desty, destz, -0.5f);
4961
4962 destz -= halfHeight;
4963
4964 // Collided with static LOS object, move back to collision point
4965 if (col)
4966 {
4967 destx -= CONTACT_DISTANCE * std::cos(angle);
4968 desty -= CONTACT_DISTANCE * std::sin(angle);
4969 dist = std::sqrt((pos.x - destx) * (pos.x - destx) + (pos.y - desty) * (pos.y - desty));
4970 }
4971 }
4972
4973 // check dynamic collision
4974 col = getWorldMap()->getObjectHitPos(GetPhase(),
4975 LocationVector(pos.x, pos.y, pos.z + halfHeight),
4976 LocationVector(destx, desty, destz + halfHeight),
4977 destx, desty, destz, -0.5f);
4978
4979 destz -= halfHeight;
4980
4981 // Collided with a gameobject, move back to collision point
4982 if (col)
4983 {
4984 destx -= CONTACT_DISTANCE * std::cos(angle);
4985 desty -= CONTACT_DISTANCE * std::sin(angle);
4986 dist = std::sqrt((pos.x - destx)*(pos.x - destx) + (pos.y - desty) * (pos.y - desty));
4987 }
4988
4989 float groundZ = VMAP_INVALID_HEIGHT_VALUE;
4990 normalizeMapCoord(pos.x);
4991 normalizeMapCoord(pos.y);
4992 updateAllowedPositionZ(destx, desty, destz, &groundZ);
4993
4994 pos.o = GetOrientation();
4995 pos.changeCoords(destx, desty, destz);
4996
4997 // position has no ground under it (or is too far away)
4998 if (groundZ <= INVALID_HEIGHT)
4999 {
5000 if (Unit* unit = ToUnit())
5001 {
5002 // unit can fly, ignore.
5003 if (unit->canFly())
5004 return;
5005
5006 // fall back to gridHeight if any
5007 float gridHeight = getWorldMap()->getGridHeight(pos.x, pos.y);
5008 if (gridHeight > INVALID_HEIGHT)
5009 {
5010 pos.z = gridHeight;
5011#if VERSION_STRING >= WotLK
5012 pos.z += unit->getHoverHeight();
5013#endif
5014 }
5015 }
5016 }
5017}

5260#else
5261void MovementInfo::readMovementInfo(ByteBuffer& data, [[maybe_unused]]uint16_t opcode, ExtraMovementStatusElement* extras /*= nullptr*/)
5262{
5263 bool hasTransportData = false,
5264 hasMovementFlags = false,
5265 hasMovementFlags2 = false;
5266
5267 MovementStatusElements* sequence = GetMovementStatusElementsSequence(sOpcodeTables.getInternalIdForHex(opcode));
5268 if (!sequence)
5269 {
5270 sLogger.failure("Unsupported MovementInfo::Read for 0x{:X} ({})!", opcode);
5271 return;
5272 }
5273
5274 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < MSE_COUNT; ++i)
5275 {
5276 MovementStatusElements element = sequence[i];
5277 if (element == MSEEnd)
5278 break;
5279
5280 if (element >= MSEGuidBit0 && element <= MSEGuidBit7)
5281 {
5282 guid[element - MSEGuidBit0] = data.readBit();
5283 continue;
5284 }
5285
5286 if (element >= MSEGuid2Bit0 && element <= MSEGuid2Bit7)
5287 {
5288 guid2[element - MSEGuid2Bit0] = data.readBit();
5289 continue;
5290 }
5291
5292 if (element >= MSETransportGuidBit0 && element <= MSETransportGuidBit7)
5293 {
5294 if (hasTransportData)
5295 transport_guid[element - MSETransportGuidBit0] = data.readBit();
5296 continue;
5297 }
5298
5299 if (element >= MSEGuidByte0 && element <= MSEGuidByte7)
5300 {
5301 if (guid[element - MSEGuidByte0])
5302 guid[element - MSEGuidByte0] ^= data.readUInt8();
5303 continue;
5304 }
5305
5306 if (element >= MSEGuid2Byte0 && element <= MSEGuid2Byte7)
5307 {
5308 if (guid2[element - MSEGuid2Byte0])
5309 guid2[element - MSEGuid2Byte0] ^= data.readUInt8();
5310 continue;
5311 }
5312
5313 if (element >= MSETransportGuidByte0 && element <= MSETransportGuidByte7)
5314 {
5315 if (hasTransportData && transport_guid[element - MSETransportGuidByte0])
5316 transport_guid[element - MSETransportGuidByte0] ^= data.readUInt8();
5317 continue;
5318 }
5319
5320 switch (element)
5321 {
5322 case MSEFlags:
5323 if (hasMovementFlags)
5324 flags = data.readBits(30);
5325 break;
5326 case MSEFlags2:
5327 if (hasMovementFlags2)
5328 flags2 = static_cast<uint16_t>(data.readBits(12));
5329 break;
5330 case MSEHasUnknownBit:
5331 data.readBit();
5332 break;
5333 case MSETimestamp:

5465void MovementInfo::writeMovementInfo(ByteBuffer& data, [[maybe_unused]]uint16_t opcode, [[maybe_unused]]float custom_speed, ExtraMovementStatusElement* extras /*= nullptr*/) const
5466{
5467 bool hasTransportData = !transport_guid.IsEmpty();
5468
5469 MovementStatusElements* sequence = GetMovementStatusElementsSequence(opcode);
5470 if (!sequence)
5471 {
5472 sLogger.failure("Unsupported MovementInfo::Write for 0x{:X}!", opcode);
5473 return;
5474 }
5475
5476 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < MSE_COUNT; ++i)
5477 {
5478 MovementStatusElements element = sequence[i];
5479
5480 if (element == MSEEnd)
5481 break;
5482
5483 if (element >= MSEGuidBit0 && element <= MSEGuidBit7)
5484 {
5485 data.writeBit(guid[element - MSEGuidBit0]);
5486 continue;
5487 }
5488
5489 if (element >= MSETransportGuidBit0 && element <= MSETransportGuidBit7)
5490 {
5491 if (hasTransportData)
5492 data.writeBit(transport_guid[element - MSETransportGuidBit0]);
5493 continue;
5494 }
5495
5496 if (element >= MSEGuidByte0 && element <= MSEGuidByte7)
5497 {
5498 if (guid[element - MSEGuidByte0])
5499 data << uint8_t((guid[element - MSEGuidByte0] ^ 1));
5500 continue;
5501 }
5502
5503 if (element >= MSETransportGuidByte0 && element <= MSETransportGuidByte7)
5504 {
5505 if (hasTransportData && transport_guid[element - MSETransportGuidByte0])
5506 data << uint8_t((transport_guid[element - MSETransportGuidByte0] ^ 1));
5507 continue;
5508 }
5509
5510 switch (element)
5511 {
5512 case MSEHasMovementFlags:
5513 data.writeBit(!flags);
5514 break;
5515 case MSEHasMovementFlags2:
5516 data.writeBit(!flags2);
5517 break;
5518 case MSEFlags:
5519 if (flags)
5520 data.writeBits(flags, 30);
5521 break;
5522 case MSEFlags2:
5523 if (flags2)
5524 data.writeBits(flags2, 12);
5525 break;
5526 case MSETimestamp:
5527 if (status_info.hasTimeStamp)
5528 data << Util::getMSTime();
5529 break;
5530 case MSEHasPitch:
5531 data.writeBit(!status_info.hasPitch);
5532 break;
5533 case MSEHasTimestamp:
5534 data.writeBit(!status_info.hasTimeStamp);
5535 break;
5536 case MSEHasUnknownBit:
5537 data.writeBit(false);
5538 break;
5539 case MSEHasFallData:
5540 data.writeBit(status_info.hasFallData);
5541 break;
5542 case MSEHasFallDirection:
5543 if (status_info.hasFallData)
5544 data.writeBit(status_info.hasFallDirection);
5545 break;
5546 case MSEHasTransportData:
5547 data.writeBit(hasTransportData);
5548 break;
5549 case MSEHasTransportTime2:
5550 if (hasTransportData)
5551 data.writeBit(status_info.hasTransportTime2);
5552 break;
5553 case MSEHasTransportTime3:
5554 if (hasTransportData)
5555 data.writeBit(status_info.hasTransportTime3);
5556 break;
5557 case MSEHasSpline:
5558 data.writeBit(status_info.hasSpline);
5559 break;
5560 case MSEHasSplineElevation:
5561 data.writeBit(!status_info.hasSplineElevation);
5562 break;
5563 case MSEPositionX:
5564 data << float(position.x);
5565 break;
5566 case MSEPositionY:
5567 data << float(position.y);
5568 break;
5569 case MSEPositionZ:
5570 data << float(position.z);
5571 break;
5572 case MSEPositionO:
5573 if (status_info.hasOrientation)
5574 data << float(normalizeOrientation(position.o));
5575 break;
5576 case MSEPitch:
5577 if (status_info.hasPitch)
5578 data << float(pitch_rate);
5579 break;
5580 case MSEHasOrientation:
5581 data.writeBit(!status_info.hasOrientation);
5582 break;
5583 case MSEFallTime:
5584 if (status_info.hasFallData)
5585 data << uint32_t(fall_time);
5586 break;
5587 case MSESplineElevation:
5588 if (status_info.hasSplineElevation)
5589 data << float(spline_elevation);
5590 break;
5591 case MSEFallHorizontalSpeed:
5592 if (status_info.hasFallData && status_info.hasFallDirection)
5593 data << float(jump_info.xyspeed);
5594 break;
5595 case MSEFallVerticalSpeed:
5596 if (status_info.hasFallData)
5597 data << float(jump_info.velocity);
5598 break;
5599 case MSEFallCosAngle:
5600 if (status_info.hasFallData && status_info.hasFallDirection)
5601 data << float(jump_info.cosAngle);
5602 break;
5603 case MSEFallSinAngle:
5604 if (status_info.hasFallData && status_info.hasFallDirection)
5605 data << float(jump_info.sinAngle);
5606 break;
5607 case MSETransportSeat:
5608 if (hasTransportData)
5609 data << int8_t(transport_seat);
5610 break;
5611 case MSETransportPositionO:
5612 if (hasTransportData)
5613 data << float(normalizeOrientation(transport_position.o));
5614 break;
5615 case MSETransportPositionX:
5616 if (hasTransportData)
5617 data << float(transport_position.x);
5618 break;
5619 case MSETransportPositionY:
5620 if (hasTransportData)
5621 data << float(transport_position.y);
5622 break;
5623 case MSETransportPositionZ:
5624 if (hasTransportData)
5625 data << float(transport_position.z);
5626 break;
5627 case MSETransportTime:
5628 if (hasTransportData)
5629 data << uint32_t(transport_time);
5630 break;
5631 case MSETransportTime2:
5632 if (hasTransportData && status_info.hasTransportTime2)
5633 data << uint32_t(transport_time2);
5634 break;
5635 case MSETransportTime3:
5636 if (hasTransportData && status_info.hasTransportTime3)
5637 data << uint32_t(fall_time);
5638 break;
5639 case MSEMovementCounter:
5640 data << uint32_t(0);
5641 break;
5642 case MSEByteParam:
5643 if (extras)
5644 extras->writeNextElement(data);
5645 else
5646 data << int8_t(byte_parameter);
5647 break;
5648 case MSECustomSpeed:
5649 data << float(custom_speed);
5650 break;
5651 default:
5652 sLogger.failure("Wrong movement status element");
5653 break;
5654 }
5655 }
